solution.p:
The long term slope of f is given by:
                    \lim_{x\to\infty}\fe{\fd{f}}{x}&=\lim_{x\to\infty}\frac{10x^4+8x^2-10x+6}{25x^4+30x^2+9}
                    &=\frac{2}{5}
                    So the slope of the skew asymptote is \frac{2}{5}.
